ğŸ”¹ Problem: Move Zeroes (Easy)
ğŸ”¹ Problem No.: #283
ğŸ”¹ Approach Used: Two Pointer Method
ğŸ” Concepts: Array Traversal, In-Place Update, Optimization

ğŸ’¡ Problem Brief:
Given an array, move all 0â€™s to the end while maintaining the relative order of non-zero elements.

âœ… Approach Explanation:
We use two pointers â€”

One (j) to iterate over the array

Another (i) to mark the position of the next non-zero element

We move all non-zero elements to the front and then fill the rest with zeroes.

ğŸ”¸ Time Complexity: O(n)
ğŸ”¸ Space Complexity: O(1)

ğŸ‘¨â€ğŸ’» C++ Code Snippet:

void moveZeroes(vector<int>& nums) {
    int i = 0;
    for (int j = 0; j < nums.size(); j++) {
        if (nums[j] != 0) {
            nums[i] = nums[j];
            i++;
        }
    }
    while (i < nums.size()) {
        nums[i] = 0;
        i++;
    }
}
